{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":1897,"name":"","username":"ucupumar","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/u/ccd318/{size}.png","created_at":"2014-07-18T15:14:24.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHello all.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWhy editor viewport camera view mask is not using -1 value?\u003cbr\u003e\nI‚Äôve use a lot of view mask setting and because of that, some objects isn‚Äôt displayed on viewport.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T00:59:50.009Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":74,"reads":17,"readers_count":16,"score":373.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":354,"topic_slug":"default-editor-viewport-camera-view-mask","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":83,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":1898,"name":"","username":"friesencr","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/friesencr/{size}/827_2.png","created_at":"2014-07-18T15:39:54.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eAs far as I can tell it is only used to filter out raycasts for objects that are reserved for the editor, which at this point are the grid and the gizmo.  If you reserve the last bit for urho you should be good. so use less then 0x80000000.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T00:59:50.069Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":18,"readers_count":17,"score":3.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":354,"topic_slug":"default-editor-viewport-camera-view-mask","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Core developer","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":15,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":1900,"name":"","username":"ucupumar","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/u/ccd318/{size}.png","created_at":"2014-07-19T09:19:38.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eIt looks like not every bit less than 0x80000000 can be used on editor viewport. Actually objects can only showed up if bit 1 (0x00000002) of view mask is valued 1. It can be 2 or 3, but not 4 or 1, etc.\u003cbr\u003e\nSo, the viewport only display objects on bit 1 view mask, everything else will not displayed. It‚Äôs strange.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAfter messing around with editor script, I found the code that responsible for this, on \u003ca href=\"http://EditorView.as\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003eEditorView.as\u003c/a\u003e line 108:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003ecamera.viewMask = 0x80000000 + (uint(1) \u0026lt;\u0026lt; index); // It's easier to only have 1 gizmo active this viewport is shared with the gizmo   \u003c/code\u003eIndex variable means active viewport. I didn‚Äôt know before that Urho Editor can use more than one viewport. So it means that on viewport 0, camera viewmask will use value of 0x80000002, and on viewport 1, it will use value of 0x80000004, etc. It explains the strange behaviour I wrote before. After I test using more than viewport, viewport 0 can only display bit 1, viewport 1 can only display bit 2, etc.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf I commented line 108 and use this code:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003e//camera.viewMask = 0x80000000 + (uint(1) \u0026lt;\u0026lt; index); // It's easier to only have 1 gizmo active this viewport is shared with the gizmo\n camera.viewMask = -1;\u003c/code\u003eEditor will display anything view mask I input (expect ‚Äò0‚Äô of course). As far as I tested, the gizmo and grid still works as usual too.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWhy camera editor isn‚Äôt just use value of -1? I means why use different mask on different viewport camera?\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T00:59:50.219Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":18,"readers_count":17,"score":3.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":354,"topic_slug":"default-editor-viewport-camera-view-mask","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"http://EditorView.as","internal":false,"reflection":false,"clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":83,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":1901,"name":"","username":"friesencr","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/friesencr/{size}/827_2.png","created_at":"2014-07-19T12:38:07.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eThe reason they use a different mask was to hide the gizmo.  Now that the pre render viewport callbacks exist that could be fixed to do without.  I did write that code and I am a bit of a peanut brain.  I will do the refactor.  It will still have to be \u0026gt;0x80000000 but i can atleast get rid of the viewport specific stuff.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T00:59:50.288Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":15,"readers_count":14,"score":3.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":354,"topic_slug":"default-editor-viewport-camera-view-mask","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Core developer","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":15,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":1902,"name":"","username":"friesencr","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/friesencr/{size}/827_2.png","created_at":"2014-07-19T13:57:58.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eNow every camera is using the same mask.  The update is on master.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T00:59:50.348Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":14,"readers_count":13,"score":2.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":354,"topic_slug":"default-editor-viewport-camera-view-mask","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Core developer","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":15,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":1903,"name":"","username":"ucupumar","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/u/ccd318/{size}.png","created_at":"2014-07-19T14:38:59.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eYeah thanks friesencr! You‚Äôre the best!  :mrgreen:\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T00:59:50.413Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":13,"readers_count":12,"score":2.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":354,"topic_slug":"default-editor-viewport-camera-view-mask","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":83,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":1904,"name":"","username":"ucupumar","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/u/ccd318/{size}.png","created_at":"2014-07-19T14:56:18.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eWait a minute, now I can‚Äôt even change object view mask to anything expect -1 (0xFFFFFFFF)\u003cbr\u003e\nAfter checked the diff, I see:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003ecamera.viewMask = 0x80000000; // It's easier to only have 1 gizmo active this viewport is shared with the gizmo\u003c/code\u003eNow every camera use 0x80000000, it means active the only active bit is bit 31.\u003cbr\u003e\nWhy don‚Äôt you just use -1 to camera view mask? What kind of gizmo hiding you‚Äôre talking about?\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":7,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T00:59:50.495Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":3,"reads":11,"readers_count":10,"score":17.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":354,"topic_slug":"default-editor-viewport-camera-view-mask","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":83,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":1905,"name":"","username":"friesencr","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/friesencr/{size}/827_2.png","created_at":"2014-07-19T15:20:55.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eThe gizmo is sized relative to distance you are away from it.  That way when you are really far away you can still see it.  However it is only sized based on the active viewport.  If you are zoomed out on the active viewport and have another view seeing the gizmo can take up the whole screen, which is kind of funny to watch but not very useful.  The sizing code could probably be put in the begin viewport render callback.  The gizmo only being in the active view is there slightly because of usability too.  I don‚Äôt have strong feelings about that.  I personally found it to be a slightly nice indicator.  I did changed the camera viewmask to -1, its on master.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis is definitely better thank you for the feedback.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":8,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T00:59:50.559Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":10,"readers_count":9,"score":2.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":354,"topic_slug":"default-editor-viewport-camera-view-mask","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_e